description: Moreish meatballs are quick and easy to prepare with this veggie-packed recipe. Make our healthier spaghetti and meatballs for a hearty family dinner.
keywords: Meatballs,Low saturated fat,Seafood free,Tree nut free,Low sugar,Sesame free,Beef,Zucchini,High protein,May 2022,Low fat
name: Healthier Beef Meatballs Recipe | Woolworths
recipeIngredient: 500g Macro grass fed Australian beef mince
1 bunch continental parsley, leaves picked, 1/2 finely chopped

recipeInstructions.text: Place mince, zucchini and carrot in a large bowl. Add garlic paste, breadcrumbs and chopped parsley, then season with pepper and mix until well combined. Roll level tablespoons of mince mixture into balls, then place on a large baking paper-lined tray. Refrigerate for 10 minutes to chill.
Spray a large, deep frying pan with oil, then heat over medium-high heat. Cook meatballs, in 2 batches, for 5 minutes, turning, or until browned. Transfer to a plate and cover to keep warm.

Heat pan over medium heat. Cook onion for 5 minutes, stirring, or until softened. Add sauce and meatballs, then bring to the boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer for 5 minutes or until sauce has thickened and meatballs are cooked through.
Meanwhile, cook spaghetti in a saucepan of boiling water according to packet instructions. Drain.
Add spaghetti to frying pan. Toss to combine. Serve topped with parmesan and remaining parsley.
